OL,3,CMedical professionals say 'greater
OL,4,Cclarity' needed over assisted dying
OL,5,CBills
OL,7,FWhile the medical body adopts a
OL,8,Fneutral stance towards assisted dying,
OL,9,Fof the 635 medical professionals
OL,10,Fsurveyed, almost half (49%) said they
OL,11,Fwere either opposed to this, or were
OL,12,Fleaning towards opposing the change `
OL,13,Fwith two fifths (41%) saying they
OL,14,Fsupport it, or were leaning towards
OL,15,Fsupporting it.
OL,17,FHowever three fifths of those surveyed
OL,18,F(59%) said that assessing if a patient
OL,19,Fwas voluntarily requesting help to
OL,20,Fdie, and was not being coerced into
OL,21,Fthis, could pose a "major challenge".
