OL,7,FMeanwhile Mr McArthur's Bill finished
OL,8,Fits second stage at Holyrood this
OL,9,Fweek, with MSPs on the Scottish
OL,10,FParliament's Health Committee having
OL,11,Fdebated almost 300 proposed changes. A
OL,12,Ffinal vote on the proposals is now
OL,13,Fexpected to take place early in 2026.
OL,15,FDr Morven McElroy, honorary secretary
OL,16,Fat the Royal College of Physicians and
OL,17,FSurgeons of Glasgow, said: "As a
OL,18,Fcollege, we have a neutral position on
OL,19,Fthe principle of assisted dying.
OL,26,@yD@\OU
