OL,5,CBills
OL,7,F"I am also reassured that the numbers
OL,8,Fof those willing to participate would
OL,9,Fensure that terminally ill adults in
OL,10,FScotland who wished to make this
OL,11,Fchoice would be able to do so and was
OL,12,Fespecially struck that respondents who
OL,13,Fwere willing to participate stated
OL,14,Fthat assisted dying is inherently part
OL,15,Fof healthcare in 'enabling access to a
OL,16,Fsafe and dignified death'.
OL,18,F"I note that the survey took place
OL,19,Fahead of the Health, Social Care and
OL,20,FSport Committee's Stage 2 scrutiny of
OL,21,Fmy Bill.
