OL,3,CMedical professionals say 'greater
OL,4,Cclarity' needed over assisted dying
OL,5,CBills
OL,7,F"Additionally, the Bill now contains
OL,8,Fprovision that ensures there is no
OL,9,Fdetriment to those for participating
OL,10,For not participating and a "no-duty to
OL,11,Fparticipate directly in assisted
OL,12,Fdying" clause for health care
OL,13,Fprofessionals.
OL,15,F"Alongside the training that any
OL,16,Fhealth care professional will complete
OL,17,Fin order to undertake assisted dying
OL,18,Fprovision, this has the effect of
OL,19,Fcreating an 'opt in' system rather
OL,20,Fthan it being the responsibility of
OL,21,Fmedical professionals to 'opt out'.
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@\OUtD@FO]wD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
